<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dip" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dip,</orth> vb. tr. to plunge, to immerse: followed by <emph>in</emph>: <cit><quote>this cloth thou dippedst in blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.157" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 157</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 19</bibl> Absolutely: <cit><quote>who can call him his friend that --s in the same dish?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 2, 73</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>